            <instructions>
                <p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Click the <c>Show Relation</c> button. What do you notice about the arrows leaving element <m>a</m> in the Domain?
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Based on the animation, why does having multiple arrows originating from a single input violate the definition of a function?
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Now, click the <c>Show Function</c> button. Observe the arrows leaving elements <m>b</m> and <m>c</m>.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Is it permissible for two different inputs in the Domain to point to the exact same output in the Codomain? How does this differ from the first example?
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
            </instructions>
        </interactive>
    </exploration>
    </introduction>

